From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Spyros Seimenis <sespiros@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 00:44:30 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] runtime: detect hypervisor exit and cancel pending agent dial
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Combines improvements from multiple investigation rounds:

1. Set q.stopped on QEMU exit (LogAndWait) and guest panic
   (handleGuestPanic via GUEST_PANICKED QMP event). This ensures
   the monitor's Check() immediately detects the failure without
   trying to reconnect to the dead QMP socket. Implements the TODO
   from https://github.com/kata-containers/kata-containers/issues/1026.

2. Cancel the sandbox context when the hypervisor exits, aborting
   the agent vsock connection dial that otherwise blocks for the
   full dial_timeout (~90 seconds). The kernel's vhost_vsock_dev_release
   only resets connected sockets, not sockets in TCP_SYN_SENT state,
   so each vsock.Dial() blocks for 2 seconds (VSOCK_DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT)
   before returning ETIMEDOUT, and commonDialer retries in a tight
   loop for the entire dial_timeout.

3. Make commonDialer context-aware: check ctx.Done() between dial
   retries and in the main select. Also fixes a latency bug in the
   original code where "cancel <- true" blocks for up to 2 seconds
   when the dial goroutine is inside vsock.Dial().

Implementation:
- Add markStopped() method (guarded by sync.Once) that sets q.stopped
  and calls the onStop callback.
- Add SetOnStop() for thread-safe callback registration.
- Create cancellable context in newSandbox() (before agent.init so
  k.ctx inherits it). Wire q.SetOnStop to the cancel function in
  startVM() before StartVM() to avoid race with LogAndWait.
- Thread context.Context through the dialer type, commonDialer,
  VsockDialer, HybridVSockDialer, RemoteSockDialer, and
  MockHybridVSockDialer.
- Clean up vmCancel on sandbox creation failure to avoid context
  goroutine leak.

With this change, when QEMU exits:
- LogAndWait calls markStopped -> sets q.stopped, cancels context
- commonDialer's goroutine finishes current vsock.Dial() (max 2s)
  then checks ctx.Done() and exits
- Main select sees ctx.Done() and returns immediately
- Total: ≤2 seconds from QEMU exit to error propagation (was ~90s)
